      "content": "You're welcome! It's great to hear that you're thinking about potential hidden risks. Contracts can indeed have some tricky parts that aren't immediately obvious. Here are a few things to watch out for:\n\n1. **Ambiguous Language**: Look for any vague or unclear terms. Ambiguity can often be exploited, so it's important to seek clarification on any terms that aren't clear to you.\n\n2. **Excessive Liability**: Be wary of clauses that seem to put an unreasonable amount of liability on you. While some level of risk is normal, excessive or disproportionate liability can be a red flag.\n\n3. **Waiver of Rights**: Check for any clauses that might limit your ability to seek legal recourse or waive your rights in certain situations. These can sometimes be buried in the fine print.\n\n4. **Exclusivity Clauses**: These can restrict your ability to work with other clients or consult with other professionals, which might limit your future opportunities.\n\n5. **Governing Law and Jurisdiction**: Make sure you understand which laws apply and where any disputes will be resolved. Sometimes, this can be in a location that's inconvenient or unfamiliar to you.\n\n6. **Force Majeure**: This clause can excuse parties",
